COMMENT     REVIEWED REFSEQ: This record has been curated by NCBI staff in
            collaboration with Nazneen Rahman, Arleen Auerbach. The reference
            sequence was derived from AC008870.8.
            This sequence is a reference standard in the RefSeqGene project.
            
            Summary: This gene encodes a protein that may function in tumor
            suppression. This protein binds to and colocalizes with the breast
            cancer 2 early onset protein (BRCA2) in nuclear foci and likely
            permits the stable intranuclear localization and accumulation of
            BRCA2. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008].
